1 15-10-38.2. Skilled workforce scholarship program - Skilled workforce scholarship
2 fund - Continuing appropriation - Report.
3 1. There is created in the state treasury the skilled workforce scholarship fund. The fund
4 consists of moneys transferred into the fund by the legislative assembly, matching
5 funds received, and scholarship repayments. Moneys in the fund are appropriated to
6 the state board of higher education on a continuing basis for the purpose of providing
7 grants to institutions of higher education related to skilled workforce scholarships.
8 Institutions of higher education include institutions under the control of the state board
9 of higher education, North Dakota nonpublic accredited institutions of higher
10 education, tribally controlled community colleges, state-approved educator training
11 programs, and North Dakota institutions approved to operate by the North Dakota
12 board of career and technical education. The state board of higher education may
13 transfer money between this fund and the skilled workforce student loan repayment
14 program fund established in section 15-10-38.1.
15 2. The state board of higher education shall adopt policies and procedures to develop,
16 implement, promote, and administer a skilled workforce scholarship program in
17 cooperation with the Bank of North Dakota and the North Dakota workforce
18 development council with the intent of attracting and retaining individuals for
19 professional or technical skills in high demand in this state.
20 3. The North Dakota workforce development council in cooperation with job service North
21 Dakota shall use available labor market information to determine annually the eligible
22 high-demand professional and technical skills and emerging occupations in this state.
23 4. The state board of higher education and the workforce development council shall
24 compile a list of qualifying educational programs annually. A qualifying educational
25 program is a program resulting in attainment of an associate's degree or lower
26 credential program that may be completed within four semesters, six quarters, or the
27 final two years of a baccalaureate program. A qualifying educational program also
28 must pertain to the professional and technical skills and emerging occupations in high
29 demand in this state, as determined under subsection 3. Qualifying educational
30 programs may include degree or certificate programs.
