13 SECTION 5. A new section to chapter 15-62.4 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
14 and enacted as follows:
15 Supplemental state grant award.
16 1. An individual eligible for a student financial assistance grant under this chapter may be
17 considered for a supplemental state grant award if the individual's total family income,
18 as identified on the free application for federal student aid, is no more than eighty
19 thousand dollars.
20 2. A supplemental state grant award may not be provided for the summer term.
21 3. Each semester or quarter, the state board of higher education shall provide to an
22 eligible student a supplemental state grant award in an amount that, combined with
23 the individual's student financial assistance grant and any federal Pell grant award,
24 does not exceed the tuition charged at the institution in which the student is enrolled.
25 The amount may not exceed the highest undergraduate semester tuition charged at
26 an institution of higher education under the control of the state board of higher
27 education.
28 4. If funding appropriated for this program is not sufficient to pay the full amount of the
29 grant award under subsection 3, the state board of higher education may prorate the
30 amount.
