8 SECTION 7. AMENDMENT. Section 15-63-05 of the North Dakota Century Code is
9 amended and reenacted as follows:
10 15-63-05. Scholarship payments - Conditions.
11 Upon the award of a scholarship, the recipient is eligible for a credit at the enrolling
12 institution of higher learning or accredited career and technical education program with a
13 physical presence in this state. The scholarship may be applied to tuition, fees, room and board,
14 books and supplies, and other educational expenses not to exceed six hundred sixty-seven
15 dollars per quarter or clock-hour term or one thousand dollars per semester. Awards may not
16 exceed two thousand dollars in any academic year and may not be issued in excess of the total
17 cost of attendance, as determined by the institution of higher education, when considering all
18 financial aid sources. The board for Native American scholarships may reduce the amount of
19 any scholarship to accord with individual financial need or funds available. The board for Native
20 American scholarships may set a priority application date. At the beginning of each quarter,
21 clock-hour term, or semester, the North Dakota university system shall verify enrollment and
22 other eligibility criteria set forth by the state board for Native American scholarships for awarded
23 applicants before issuing payment to the enrolling institution. After the enrolling institution has
24 deducted the amount due to the institution, the remaining balance must be distributed to the
25 awarded applicant for necessary expenses during the quarter, clock-hour term, or semester.
